<TITLE> DGEN continues downward after record losses </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 03 (bdnews24.com)The market continued to fall in the opening session Monday after the DGEN suffered record losses the previous day. The trading system at the country's prime bourse was brought to a halt at about 11.20 am due to technical reasons. It resumed after an hour with trading set to continue till 3:00 pm, according to a notification by the DSE. The market began to gain pace at the midday. At 12.21 pm the DGEN or general index had fallen 73.61 points or 2.55 percent to 2805.12. The DSI or all share price index was at 2372.19, down 61.72 points or 2.53 percent. At 12.29 pm, BRAC Bank emerged at the top of the share value board, selling at Tk 1528.75 from Sunday's closing price of Tk 1538.5. UCBL followed BRAC Bank, selling at Tk 4438 from Tk 4716.75 Sunday close of trade. Market heavyweight Power Grid Company of Bangladesh also declined, down to Tk 689 from Sunday's closing price of Tk 683.75. Uttara Bank, one of the most active shares on the market, was down at Tk 4381 from Sunday's Tk 4466.75. Other scrips on the top ten by value boardIslami Bank Perpetual Bond, Summit Power, Trust Bank, AB Bank, Islami Bank and Lafarge Surma Cementcontinued to fall. bdne
